Statistical Model

See equation @ref(eq:eqn1) and @ref(eq:eqn2) for the statistical models we use.

\[\begin{equation} y = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x + \varepsilon (\#eq:eqn1) \end{equation}\]

\[\begin{align} Y_z & = f_z(S) + g_z(N) + h_z(X,Y) + \varepsilon_z \\ & = \sum_{i=1}^k \phi_k(S) + g_z(N) + h_z(X,Y) + \varepsilon_z (\#eq:eqn2) \end{align}\]

Our target coefficient is \(\beta_1\) (in-line math).
